articles.author: @techbubble
articles.description:
You and I, Around the World

You and I, around the world
We walk freely
Without the trauma
Of being stopped and beaten
For letting down our hair
And being ourselves

You and I, around the world
We breathe freely
Without the suffocation
Of a brutal government
Crazed with power
And religious zeal

You and I, around the world
We live freely
Without the heartbreak
Of living with friends, family
Gone one day, without a trace
And no good-byes

You and I, around the world
We talk freely
Without the fear
Of that knock on the door
To be dragged into the night
And silenced forever

You and I, around the world
We stay silent
Without the agony
Of our youth murdered
For protesting injustice
And demanding freedom

Mirhashemi, Kazemi, Yaghoubi
They are gone

But you and I, around the world
We go on! üñ§
